{
  "style": "",
  "texts": [
    "Recently, a multitask learning method was used to obtain CVs for enhanced sampling of rare events.",
    "This method addresses three tasks simultaniously: (i) dimensionality reduction in the form of a latent space is performed by a common upstream encoder, then separate downstream parts use this latent space to (ii) assign a basin class labels using a basin classifier, and (iii) predict potential energy using a potential energy predictor.",
    "The model is trained by combining short MD trajectories confined to the basins or containing transitions.",
    "A joint loss function is used for training, which combines the loss functions for each task.",
    "To obtain free energy landscapes, an iterative training procedure is followed."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}